# Files to exclude from `gcloud builds submit` source uploads.
#
# Cloud Build untars the source and then Dockerfile COPYs pick pieces
# out of it. We keep the upload small by stripping Rust build
# artifacts and IDE/OS noise, while deliberately including the temper
# submodule's working tree (the Dockerfile needs it to build the
# temper binary with the ADR-0056 branch checked out).

# Rust / Cargo
**/target/
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.bak

# IDE
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# macOS
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store

# Git internals — submodule working trees DO get uploaded (that's the
# whole point) but .git dirs are noise.
.git/
**/.git/
